        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Saint Paul</placeName>
                <date>October 20 5623</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <sic>
                    <addressee>Doctor vice</addressee>
                </sic>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I am one of them,<lb/> who never read your paper, for this reason,
                    <hi rend="underline">should</hi><lb/> there be any thing <hi rend="underline"
                    >worth</hi> of reading, surely, I have<lb/> read it before, and to spend time in
                reading the ideas<lb/> of your <hi rend="underline">own</hi>! Which is indeed very
                poor, that would<lb/> be, to waste away time, of which I am able thank God<lb/> to
                employ it in some thing <hi rend="underline">better</hi> than the fabulous<lb/>
                paper, as <hi rend="underline">you know me</hi>. But having been represented<lb/>
                with one of your scandalous paper, and having observed<lb/> your anxiety to know my
                where abouts is, and seeing<lb/> that none comply with your wish, I thought it
                proper<lb/> to inform you myself, and to let you know, that I<lb/> was engaged in
                this worthy congregation, after your unworthy<lb/> paper was read, to convince you
                of the truth of the German<lb/> proverb, “<add>?</add><lb/>
                <add>?</add>” Sir! You say that I am<lb/>
                <sic>travling</sic> about as a cheat, <sic>As</sic> a convert. <sic>are</sic> you
                able sir<lb/> to point out any place where I said that I am so or so?<lb/> I will
                consider you one of the two; either as the <persName>king<lb/> Solomon</persName>
                says <add>פתי מאמין לכל דבר</add>, or should it be of your own<lb/> fabrication, to
                injure a person merely because he<lb/> is not of your opinion, you deny the coming
                of a Messiah<lb/> and I believe in his coming, you deny the <sic>resurection</sic>,
                and I<lb/> believe it, you say that this is not the same Bible which<lb/> the
                Almighty gave it to us through <persName>Moses</persName>, and I believe it</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>And above all, in the name of conscience, you know<lb/> me, and all what it was
                spoken about me, and why<lb/> have you chosen me to be one of your <add>בית
                    דין</add> to make<lb/> the <add>גיורת</add>, why have you given me
                    <add>קבלה</add>? Why have you<lb/>
                <sic>deffended</sic> me against the man who spoke ill, of the<lb/>
                <persName>Rev Mr. Rosenfield</persName>, of yourself and of me?
                <sic>indeed</sic><lb/> sir, I see that my opinion of you from the very<lb/> first
                time I knew you was true, I kept you for an<lb/>
                <add>איש משוגע</add>, a <add>הפכפך</add>. It is indeed true the saying of the<lb/>
                <add>גר"א</add>—which in the name of <add>רבי מאיר</add> says he always<lb/>
                considered a man by his name, and so I consider<lb/> you, it is not for nothing that
                your name is vice,<lb/> but because you are the foundation of all viciousness<lb/>
                since you came to this country the true faith found<lb/> its end, you trod true
                religion under foot, you made<lb/>
                <placeName>Israel</placeName>
                <hi rend="underline">light</hi>
                <sic>istaed</sic> of Israelite, in short sir you<lb/> are the man who can do good to
                none, and even to<lb/> yourself without injuring another. Now sir, I will tell<lb/>
                you what you are if none told you yet, you are no Talmudist at<lb/> all and your
                Philosophy indeed while a child I knew it.<lb/> You can only fool ignorant man, but
                among learned<lb/> what do you know? nothing—know therefore that it is<lb/> this
                only time I write to answer you, and from now you can<lb/> write whatever you
                please, no answer will be given to you<lb/> and this time I answer you only that you
                should not say<lb/> that you silenced me, and to show you that your slandering<lb/>
                can do me no harm Please God, you have great <add>חוצפה</add><lb/> because you are
                sure of being engaged for life, and I am sure<lb/> in the help of the true living
                God of <placeName>Israel</placeName>. <persName role="author">E.
                Marcuson</persName>.</p>
        </body>
